               <msContents n="1">
<!--increment n attribute for ms containing multiple ms items-->
                  <summary>This illustrated Nepalese paper manuscript, dated 1838 CE (Nepāla Saṃvat 958 written on the flyleaf), contains the first portion a Tantric
                     Buddhist text called <title xml:lang="san" type="general">Ādiyogasamādhi</title> (see <ref type="extant_mss"
                          target="http://cudl.lib.cam.ac.uk/view/MS-ADD-01278/1">Add.1278</ref>), belonging to the
                     <title>Sarvadurgatipariśodhana</title> cycle. Most of the textual
                     material of the present work is included in the so-called Version B of
                     the <title xml:lang="san">Sarvadurgatipariśodhanatantra</title> (see
                     Skorupski 1983: xviii), where it susbtitues the 'Basic Tantra'
                     (consisting of the description of the ritual <term xml:lang="san">maṇḍala</term>). 
                  </summary>

                  <msItem n="1" defective="unknown">
                     <title xml:lang="san">Ādiyogasamādhi</title>
                     <textLang mainLang="san">Sanskrit.</textLang>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>

